  "architecture": {
    "overview": "NCE Events is a Frappe app that renders configurable multi-panel data explorer pages. It has a Python API layer and two frontend generations: V1 (vanilla JS class-based) and V2 (Vue 3 SFC with Vite build). Both share SMS/Email dialogs from V1. Depends on nce_sync app. V2 supports optional frozen Form Dialogs for editing panel rows without leaving the panel page.",
    "data_flow": "Frappe Page (panel_page / panel_page_v2) → JS/Vue → frappe.call() → api/panel_api_pkg/, api/messaging.py, api/tags.py, api/reports.py, api/form_dialog/ → Frappe ORM → MariaDB",
    "key_patterns": [
      "V2 Vue app built separately: npm run build in public/js/panel_page_v2/ then bench build",
      "V2 reuses V1 SmsDialog, EmailDialog, and ai_tools.js at runtime — do NOT duplicate",
      "Python helpers follow snake_case private convention (_helper_name) — check AGENTS.md before adding",
      "frozenset used for fieldtype/fieldname skip sets",
      "Tag system uses Jinja template tags with gender-conditional pronouns",
      "Form Dialog: frozen_meta_json (snapshot of frappe.get_meta fields) is parsed by parseLayout.js + rendered by PanelFormDialog.vue. Only DocTypes in WP Tables are eligible.",
      "Form Dialog buttons: script text is copied from Desk at capture/rebuild time — not live-linked. Rebuild is manual."
    ]
  },
